* From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|acorden|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|acorder|lang=fro}} (compare modern French {{term|accord|accord|lang=fr}} and {{term|accorder|lang=en}}), from {{etyl|VL.}} {{term|accordo|accordō|to be heart to heart with|lang=la}}, formed from {{etyl|la}} {{term|ad|lang=en}} + {{term|cord||heart}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# Agreement or [[concurrence]] of opinion, will, or action.
#* '''1769''', ''[[s:Bible_(King_James)|The King James Bible - Oxford Standard Text]]'', [[s:Bible_(King_James)/Acts#Chapter_1|Acts 1:14]]
#*: These all continued with one '''accord''' in prayer.
# A [[harmony]] in sound, [[pitch]] and [[tone]]; [[concord]].
#* '''17th''' '''century''', "The Self-Subsistence of the Soul", [[w:John Davies (poet)|Sir John Davies]],
#*: Those sweet '''accords''' are even the angels' lays.
# Agreement or harmony of things in general.
# {{context|legal}} An agreement between parties in [[controversy]], by which satisfaction for an injury is [[stipulated]], and which, when [[executed]], prevents a lawsuit.
# {{context|international law}} An international agreement.
#: The Geneva '''Accord''' of 1954 ended the French-Indochinese War.
# {{obsolete}} [[assent|Assent]]
# Voluntary or spontaneous impulse to act.

